**THIS FILE MUST BE READ FIRST BY ALL AI AGENTS**

## WHAT IS THIS?

This is the AI manifest for **bqniser** — a tool that detects array computation
patterns in existing code (loops, maps, folds) and rewrites them as optimised
BQN array primitives via the CBQN runtime.  Part of the hyperpolymath -iser
family (https://github.com/hyperpolymath/iseriser).

BQN (by Marshall Lochbaum) is an array language with first-class functions,
trains, under/structural-under combinators, rank polymorphism, and leading-axis
theory.  BQNiser generates BQN code and a Zig FFI bridge to CBQN so users get
10-100x array operation speedups without learning BQN.

## CANONICAL LOCATIONS (UNIVERSAL RULE)

### Machine-Readable Metadata: `.machine_readable/` ONLY

These 6 a2ml files MUST exist in `.machine_readable/6a2/` directory ONLY:
1. **STATE.a2ml** - Project state, progress, blockers
2. **META.a2ml** - Architecture decisions, governance
3. **ECOSYSTEM.a2ml** - Position in ecosystem, relationships
4. **AGENTIC.a2ml** - AI agent interaction patterns
5. **NEUROSYM.a2ml** - Neurosymbolic integration config
6. **PLAYBOOK.a2ml** - Operational runbook

**CRITICAL:** If ANY of these files exist in the root directory, this is an ERROR.

