## REPOSITORY STRUCTURE

This repo follows the **Dual-Track** architecture:

```
bqniser/
├── 0-AI-MANIFEST.a2ml         # THIS FILE (start here)
├── README.adoc                 # What bqniser does, architecture, BQN primer
├── ROADMAP.adoc                # Phase 0-6 development plan
├── CONTRIBUTING.adoc           # Contribution guide
├── Cargo.toml                  # Rust CLI dependencies
├── Justfile                    # Task runner
├── Containerfile               # OCI build (Chainguard base)
├── LICENSE                     # PMPL-1.0-or-later
├── src/
│   ├── main.rs                 # CLI entry (init, validate, generate, build, run)
│   ├── lib.rs                  # Library API
│   ├── manifest/               # bqniser.toml parser and validator
│   ├── codegen/                # BQN expression emitter + FFI glue generator
│   ├── core/                   # Pattern detection engine (AST analysis)
│   ├── definitions/            # BQN primitive definitions and semantics
│   ├── bridges/                # CBQN runtime bridge
│   └── interface/              # Verified Interface Seams
│       ├── abi/                # Idris2 ABI — BQN types, array layout, CBQN FFI
│       │   ├── Types.idr       # ArrayRank, BQNPrimitive, Train, Modifier, Under
│       │   ├── Layout.idr      # BQN array memory layout (header+shape+data)
│       │   └── Foreign.idr     # CBQN C API declarations (eval, call, read, write)
│       ├── ffi/                # Zig FFI — CBQN embedding bridge
│       │   ├── build.zig       # Build config (shared + static libbqniser)
│       │   ├── src/main.zig    # CBQN init/eval/call/read/write/free
│       │   └── test/           # ABI compliance integration tests
│       └── generated/          # Auto-generated C headers from Idris2
├── tests/                      # Rust integration tests
├── examples/                   # Example bqniser.toml manifests
├── verification/               # Formal verification artifacts
├── container/                  # Stapeln container ecosystem
├── docs/
│   ├── architecture/           # TOPOLOGY.md, THREAT-MODEL.adoc
│   ├── theory/                 # BQN array theory, leading-axis, trains
│   └── practice/               # User guides, pattern catalogue
└── .machine_readable/          # ALL machine-readable metadata (6a2, policies, etc.)
```

## CORE INVARIANTS

1. **No state file duplication** - Root must NOT contain STATE.a2ml, META.a2ml, etc.
2. **Single source of truth** - `.machine_readable/` is authoritative
3. **No stale metadata** - If root state files exist, they are OUT OF DATE
4. **License consistency** - All code PMPL-1.0-or-later unless platform requires MPL-2.0
5. **Author attribution** - Always "Jonathan D.A. Jewell <j.d.a.jewell@open.ac.uk>"
6. **Container images** - MUST use Chainguard base (`cgr.dev/chainguard/wolfi-base:latest` or `cgr.dev/chainguard/static:latest`)
7. **Container runtime** - Podman, never Docker. Files are `Containerfile`, never `Dockerfile`
8. **Container orchestration** - `selur-compose`, never `docker-compose`
9. **BQN rewrites require proofs** - No BQN codegen without Idris2 equivalence proof
10. **CBQN access via Zig only** - All CBQN C API calls go through the Zig FFI bridge

